  "original_title": "Sri Lanka to revise water tariffs to reflect operational costs",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to revise water tariffs to reflect operational costs",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s cabinet of ministers has approved a proposal to revise water and sewage charges to reflect the Water Supply and Drainage Board\u2019s recurring operational costs and working capital loan obligations.",
        "A statement from the government information department said on Tuesday August 09 that a tariff revision was deemed necessary to ensure an interrupted supply of water.",
        "Cabinet spokesman Minister Bandula Gunawardena called it a cost-reflective price formula.",
        "According to the Central Bank annual report, in 2021, the water board recorded an operating loss of 3.1 billion rupees compared to the loss of 370.5 million rupees recorded in the previous year, owing to increases in operation and maintenance costs during the period under review.",
        "Sri Lanka is going through its worst economic crisis since Independence, with high inflation adding to public woes. (Colombo/Aug09/2022)"
      ],
